OL,6,FHe was convicted with a second man of
OL,7,Fconspiring to sell 44 ninth century
OL,8,Fcoins worth #766,000 and jailed for
OL,9,Ffive years and two months at Durham
OL,10,FCrown Court in May 2023.
OL,12,FThe coins, which were never declared
OL,13,Fas treasure, were believed to have
OL,14,Fbeen buried by a Viking and included
OL,15,Ftwo extremely rare examples of two-
OL,16,Fheaded coins, showing Alfred of Wessex
OL,17,Fand Ceolwulf II of Mercia.
