OL,6,F"He knew that these coins were stolen
OL,7,Ftreasure and instead of choosing to
OL,8,Freport a crime, he chose to try and
OL,9,Fprofit from it.
OL,11,F"The CPS worked with the police to
OL,12,Fvalue his criminal benefit from the
OL,13,Fattempted selling of these rare Anglo-
OL,14,FSaxon coins, which should have been
OL,15,Fgiven to the Crown.
OL,17,F"The Confiscation Order set by the
OL,18,FJudge reflects all the assets
OL,19,Favailable to the defendants.
